                  <birth notBefore="0329" notAfter="0330"/>
                  <floruit>A  saint and doctor of the church, he was an important figure in the 4th century strife against Arianism, an organizer of the monastic life and a prolific writer.
                     Excerpts of his works are extant in Ethiopic. <persName ref="PRS2546Basilth">Basil the Great</persName> came
                     from a deeply Christian Greek family, many members of which are venerated as saints. He visited all most important monastic 
                     centres in <placeName ref="LOC5833Syria">Syria</placeName> and <placeName ref="LOC4797Mesopo">Mesopotamia</placeName>, 
                     <placeName ref="LOC5068Palest">Palestine</placeName> and <placeName ref="LOC2804Egypt">Egypt</placeName>.</floruit>
                  
